# Economics and Trading System

## Player Money Management
- Each player starts with a base amount of money.
- Players can earn money through various in-game professions.
- Money management mechanics include savings, investments, and expenditures.

## Inventory System
- Players have a limited inventory space.
- Items can be categorized as consumables, tools, and resources.
- Players can organize, access, and use items from their inventory.

## Market Prices
- Prices of items fluctuate based on supply and demand.
- Players can check market trends and previous prices to make informed buying/selling decisions.
- Events and player actions can cause market shifts.

## Profession Earnings
- Different professions have varied earning potentials.
- Players can switch professions but may face a learning curve.
- Earnings can be influenced by player stats and market factors.

## Buying and Selling Mechanics
- Players can buy/sell items at designated market locations.
- Players can set their prices for selling items but must consider the market value.
- There are transaction fees for selling in the market to encourage fair pricing.